# API Response Format Rules

## Success Responses

### Read (GET)
Return raw data directly, no envelope wrapper:
```json
// GET /api/work-orders
{ "data": [...], "total": 342, "skip": 0, "limit": 20 }

// GET /api/work-orders/:id
{ "id": "uuid", "title": "Fix HVAC", "status": "open", ... }
```

### Create (POST)
Return created entity with 201 status:
```typescript
res.status(201).json(result);
```

### Update (PUT/PATCH)
Return updated entity with 200 status:
```typescript
res.json(result);
```

### Delete / Restore / Bulk Operations
Return message object:
```json
{ "message": "Work Order deleted successfully" }
{ "message": "5 items deleted" }
```

### Analytics
Return raw arrays or objects:
```json
// Array for charts
[{ "month": "2026-01", "created_count": 35, "completed_count": 30 }, ...]

// Object for KPIs
{ "avg_hours": 18.5 }
```

## Error Responses

All errors use `{ detail: string }` format:
```json
{ "detail": "Work Order not found" }
{ "detail": "Cannot transition from 'completed' to 'open'" }
```

Validation errors additionally include `errors`:
```json
{
    "detail": "Validation failed",
    "errors": {
        "title": ["Required"],
        "priority": ["Invalid enum value"]
    }
}
```

## HTTP Status Codes

| Code | When | Response |
|------|------|----------|
| 200 | Successful read/update/delete | Data or message |
| 201 | Successful create | Created entity |
| 400 | Validation error / bad input | `{ detail, errors? }` |
| 401 | Missing or invalid JWT | `{ detail: "Authentication required" }` |
| 403 | Insufficient permissions | `{ detail: "Insufficient permissions" }` or `{ detail: "Insufficient access" }` |
| 404 | Entity not found | `{ detail: "Entity not found" }` |
| 409 | Conflict (duplicate) | `{ detail: "Email already registered" }` |
| 429 | Rate limit exceeded | `{ detail: "Rate limit exceeded" }` |
| 500 | Unexpected server error | `{ detail: "Internal server error" }` |

## Pagination Response Shape

```typescript
interface PaginatedResponse<T> {
    data: T[];
    total: number;   // total matching records
    skip: number;    // offset
    limit: number;   // page size
}
```

## No Response Wrapping

Do NOT wrap responses in an envelope like `{ success: true, data: ... }`. Return data directly.
